5|$|The Buddhists <b>in</b> <b>Saigon</b> {{were aware}} that a raid on the pagodas was imminent. Buddhist {{relatives}} of Special Forces and combat police personnel had tipped off the monks, and Buddhists who lived near pagodas had observed them move into {{the region in the}} lead-up. American journalists were tipped off and traveled through Saigon to visit the pagodas ahead of the raids. The pagodas had been locked by the monks in preparation for the attacks and the doors were barricaded with furniture and reinforced by nailing wooden planks across them. The monks told members of the U.S. press corps <b>in</b> <b>Saigon</b> that the raids were coming, allowing them to be more prepared for the event than the U.S. embassy.|$|E
