5|$|The French ironclad Atalante was a wooden-hulled armored {{corvette}} {{built for}} the French Navy in the mid-1860s. She played a minor role in the Franco-Prussian War of 1870, bombarded Vietnamese forts during the Battle of Thuan An in 1884 and participated in the Sino-French War of 1884–85. Atalante was reduced to reserve <b>in</b> <b>Saigon</b> in 1885 and sank there two years later after having been condemned.|$|E
5|$|Thơ was apprehended {{during the}} coup and put {{under house arrest}} while the {{plotters}} consolidated their grip on power; he was then removed from the political scene. The civilian arm of the government was replaced with Khánh appointees, and Thơ left politics, having personally enriched himself during his period in government. His activities after leaving politics are not known. He died in 1976 <b>in</b> <b>Saigon.</b>|$|E
